-- S. Korean, Jordanian Companies Win $2 Billion Project, Rai Says
-- B y   M o h a m m a d   T a y s e e r
-- 2012-02-15T12:50:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/s-korean-jordanian-companies-win-2-billion-project-rai-says.html
A South Korean company and a
Jordanian partner won approval from the Jordanian Health
Ministry to build a $2 billion medical center in Amman, Al  Rai 
reported.  The complex will include a hospital, outpatient clinics, a
five-star hotel, spas and rehabilitation and physical therapy
centers, the newspaper said, citing Azmi Hadidi, who heads the
ministry’s licensing department. Hadidi didn’t disclose the
companies’ names.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mohammad Tayseer in Amman through the Dubai newsroom at 
   mtayseer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
